cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a convolutional compressive sensing framework based on deep learning, which involves both convolutional sensing and nonlinear reconstruction. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and information theory, which suggests it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) for implementation, which suggests it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
